# wolfSSL Integration for Minix

## Overview

This directory contains the wolfSSL (formerly CyaSSL) embedded SSL/TLS library integrated into the Minix build system. wolfSSL is being used to replace OpenSSL 0.9.8 due to security concerns and the end-of-life status of OpenSSL 0.9.8.

## Directory Structure

```
crypto/external/gpl2/wolfssl/
├── Makefile              # Main wolfSSL Makefile
├── README                # This file
├── lib/                  # Library build directory
│   └── Makefile          # Library-specific Makefile
└── dist/                 # wolfSSL source distribution
    ├── src/              # wolfSSL source code
    ├── wolfssl/          # wolfSSL headers
    └── wolfcrypt/        # wolfCrypt cryptographic library
```

## Build Configuration

The wolfSSL build is configured through `crypto/Makefile.wolfssl`, which includes:

- Minix-specific configuration flags
- OpenSSL compatibility layer enablement
- Required cryptographic algorithms
- Performance optimizations
- Feature disabling for size reduction

## Building wolfSSL

To build wolfSSL as part of the Minix build system:

```bash
# From the Minix root directory
make build
```

Or to build only wolfSSL:

```bash
cd crypto/external/gpl2/wolfssl
make
```

## Configuration Options

The following wolfSSL features are enabled for Minix:

- OpenSSL compatibility layer (OPENSSL_EXTRA)
- AES-GCM, ChaCha20-Poly1305
- ECC, Curve25519, Ed25519
- DH, RSA, DSA
- SHA, SHA256, SHA512, MD5
- Fast math optimizations
- Small stack configuration

The following features are disabled to reduce size:

- MD4, RC4, PSK, HC128, Rabbit
- DES3 (can be enabled if needed)
- Old TLS versions (SSLv2, SSLv3)
- Client/Server specific builds (both enabled)

## Cross-Compilation

wolfSSL supports cross-compilation for Minix. To cross-compile:

```bash
./configure --host=i386-pc-minix \
  --enable-opensslextra \
  --enable-opensslall \
  --enable-fastmath \
  --enable-smallstack
```

